 - **Loading screen theme reach (Native loading takeover, #983):** `LoadingScreenController` now resolves and applies SW-themed loading values from `loading_screen`/`ui_theme` (background + progress track/fill/shimmer + text + font-family/font-file attempts) and raises overlay order so it fully covers the native loader path during `InitialGameLoader`. Native loading UI symbols are still not directly reachable from `LoadingScreenController`/`MainMenuThemer`/`NativeMenuInjector`, so this bead implements overlay-based coverage and documents the missing native symbol requirement in `docs/sessions/loading-screen-reskin-983-20260531.md`.
+- **MODS state styling gap noted:** the injected native MODS button still needs explicit active/selected-state theming; hover/normal styling is present, but active/select colors remain native/default. Documented in `docs/sessions/loading-screen-reskin-983-20260531.md` so the next UI pass can close that gap independently of the loading-screen work.
 
 ### Fixed — Game-Breaking Regression
 - **`startGame` RPC corrupting native `GameWorldLoaderSystem` (NRE flood)** — The `startGame` RPC in `GameBridgeServer.HandleStartGame` (introduced by nav-scripter commit 65cddb03) created a bare `Components.SingletonComponents.BeginGameWorldLoadingSingleton` ECS entity with empty/unpopulated fields to programmatically trigger world-load. DINO's native `Systems.GameWorldLoaderSystem.OnUpdate` then called `GetSingleton<>()` expecting the managed component (save path / map id / load params) populated, got null/empty, and threw a `NullReferenceException` **every frame** in `InitializationSystemGroup` — flooding the log and breaking world-load. Fix (safe revert / Option A): the RPC is now a **no-op** that returns `{success:false, disabled:true}` and never creates the bare entity; normal menu-driven world-load is unaffected. To re-enable programmatic world-load, all required singleton fields must be populated with valid values before entity creation. Live-verified: GameWorldLoaderSystem NRE count went from flooding to **0**, game loads a world normally (49014 entities, advancing frames). File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/GameBridgeServer.cs` (~L1841).
